channel.title: Possibly Corrupt Cache
channel.description: Okay, so I have officially given up... I haven't used Eclipse since about last year, so I just got back into it. I'm using this source / client http://www.rune-server.org/runescape-development/google/downloads/498167-neitiznot-rhubarb-jerba-pegasus.html -- So my problem -- I can run the server just fine, I'm running it through eclipse and everything. I think the main problem is the RSA. I changed the IP to localhost in every spot possible in the client. I also was getting the error "Encrypted id!=10" from the server console before , so I commented that out and it was to no avail. Now I just simply cannot connect. I'm not familiar with RSA at all, and would like to learn from this. My main goal here is to actually be able to LOG IN to the server. Someone claimed I needed to change the "dokeyss()" but wasn't very specific. Appreciate all help.

item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

yeah exactly what I thought.

The ObjectDef in the server is trying to read the definitions for an object (in your case, the bank booth) and it either can’t find them, or they’re just non-existent. Which would mean the getObjectDef is probably returning null, which would make sense why when trying to read the ObjectName (which would be null at this point) would throw errors.

item.title: Possibly Corrupt Cache
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Every little error you get you instantly assume the cache is corrupt. It’s funny.

If you want to test if the cache is corrupt, load it in Tom’s Cache Suite and open everything 1 by 1 (from the initial menu, you don’t need to literally open all items). If something doesn’t load, it’s corrupt. If everything loads, you’re fine.

neitiznot.cache.clip.region.ObjectDef.getObjectDef(ObjectDef.java:9)

Is your error. Looks like it’s trying to get the object information from the maps and can’t because for some reason something is null that shouldn’t be.

Post the code that handles opening the bank.

Or, better yet, post your actionhandler, I’ve seen a similar error before.

Read full topic

item.dc:creator: @Camballer Camballer
item.description:
@Camballer wrote:

Edit : New problem. So the client and server run fine now. I can login and everything. But if I use the bank booths at edgeville you get this error in the server console SEVERE: Exception during task execution. java.lang.NullPointerException at neitiznot.cache.clip.region.ObjectDef.getObjectDef(ObjectDef.java:9) at neitiznot.model.players.ActionHandler.firstClickObject(ActionHandler.java:69) at neitiznot.net.packets.impl.ClickObject$1.execute(ClickObject.java:249) at neitiznot.engine.event.CycleEventContainer.execute(CycleEventContainer.java:60) at neitiznot.engine.event.CycleEventHandler.process(CycleEventHandler.java:64) at neitiznot.engine.PulseHandler.pulse(PulseHandler.java:16) at neitiznot.Server$1.execute(Server.java:67) at neitiznot.engine.task.Task.tick(Task.java:105) at neitiznot.engine.task.TaskScheduler.run(TaskScheduler.java:100) at java.util.concurrent.Executors$RunnableAdapter.call(Unknown Source) at java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.runAndReset(Unknown Source) at java.util.concurrent.ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor$ScheduledFutureTask.access$301(Unknown Source) at java.util.concurrent.ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor$ScheduledFutureTask.run(Unknown Source) at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor.runWorker(Unknown Source) at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker.run(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source)

Could it be that the cache is corrupt? How would I go upon fixing this. Then it delays then the server dc’s and no one gets saved.

item.title: Possibly Corrupt Cache
item.dc:creator: @ExtremeX-Scape Ryley
item.description:
@ExtremeX-Scape wrote:

You need to generate a new 2048 bit public and private key pair, the public key goes in the client (typically in the stream class) and the private key pair goes in the server (typically the RS2LoginProtocolDecoder class)

Nikki released a tool which generates these keys and pretty-prints them, you can find it on Rune-Server.

Read full topic
